<TITLE> JU commemorates playwright Selim Al Din </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 14 (bdnews24.com)  Jahangir Nagar University observed the first death anniversary of playwright Selim Al-Din on Wednesday. Colleagues and students held programmes on campus in remembrance of the drama and dramatics professor whose lasting contribution to Bangla drama includes the Gram Theatre. The day's progammes started with illuminations and laying floral tributes at the playwright's portrait followed by a commemorative procession on campus. Various cultural and theatre organisations laid flowers at Selim's grave, with the JU vice chancellor, teachers of the drama department and noted theatre personalities speaking at the graveside gathering. Other programmes of the day include screening of a documentary on the playwright, a musical soiree titled Kahankatha with songs written by Selim and the staging of his famous play Shokuntala. bdnews2
